Package: arsbridge
Title: Convert Annotated TLF Shells and ADaM Spec to CDISC ARS JSON
Version: 0.1.0.9006
Authors@R:
    person("Hamid", "Tavakoli",
           email = "htavakoli@gmail.com",
           role  = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-0574-7739"))
Description: Reads a lead programmer's already-annotated TLF shell Word
    document and the study's ADaM specification Excel, and produces a
    valid CDISC Analysis Results Standard (ARS) v1.0 ARM-TS JSON file
    suitable for consumption by 'siera::readARS()'. Annotation extraction
    is style-agnostic: detects ADaM variable references whether marked by
    font colour, character formatting, brackets, or plain-text appended
    after the stub label. An LLM ('ellmer'; Anthropic, OpenAI, Gemini, or
    an OpenAI-compatible provider such as GLM) acts as the primary reader of
    variant shell layouts, separating display label from variable reference,
    and also supplies light semantic enrichment per TLF section (analysis
    type, method name, row roles). Every LLM-proposed variable is gated
    against the ADaM specification, so an out-of-spec proposal is rejected
    and flagged rather than shipped; with no API key the reader degrades to
    deterministic parsing.
